    "Body": " Calibra is building a hub of financial services, products and solutions that connect everyone, everywhere, creating greater opportunity for all. Its technical foundation is the open-sourced Libra blockchain network. Libra\u2019s mission is to create a simple, borderless global currency and financial ecosystem that empowers billions of people. Calibra Research is the research arm of Calibra, and is of great importance due to the cutting-edge nature of the technical challenges and Calibra\u2019s openness to scrutiny. Facebook's Calibra Security team is seeking a passionate and experienced leader to build out and enable the team responsible for securing Calibra infrastructure and data within Facebook. This role provides the foundation for the security of Calibra products and the financial information of potentially billions of people. The ideal candidate has broad experience developing technical visions and roadmaps for a wide variety of infrastructure areas and is adept in both setting direction and guidance for their team, as well as building the necessary partnerships across the organization to ship solutions to complex problems.MANAGER, INFRASTRUCTURE SECURITY, CALIBRA RESPONSIBILITIES Define and drive execution of vision and technical strategy of Calibra\u2019s infrastructure security Build and develop a high performing team in a fast and continuously changing environment Enable a team of security engineers to engage with multiple infrastructure partners in discovering and addressing infrastructure security problems that affect Calibra services Influence cross-functional partners and roadmaps to continuously tighten the security posture of Calibra and overall Facebook infrastructure Support geographically distributed engineering and security teams Assess and present infrastructure security risk, solutions and tradeoffs to Calibra leadership that enables risk-based decision makingMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 10+ years of work experience in infrastructure or security engineering, including 3+ years of proven hands-on technical management experience of engineers Proven experience in shaping technical strategies for complex problems and executing against them Proven experience building productive relationships with partners and leadership Breadth of technical experience across various infrastructure and security areas and running in large production environments B.S. or M.S. Computer Science or related field, or equivalent experiencePREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS Experience recruiting and managing geographically distributed technical teams, including performance management Experience distilling complex technical information and conveying to different types of audiences that enables decisioning Demonstrated experience for solving complex, systemic issues that require creative thinking and solutions FinTech industry experience Blockchain infrastructure and crypto currency experience Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started. Facebook is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at accommodations-ext@fb.com. ", 
